Imo state governor, Hope Uzodinma, and Senator Rochas Okorocha have hugged and shook hands after meeting at an event.  It was gathered that the incident happened at a public function in Abuja today, February 10. Many people believe that this could be sign that the two have reconciled. Okorocha who arrived for the event late, went around to greet other important dignitaries. When he got to where Governor Uzodinma was seated, the governor got up from his seat, and both shook hands and hugged each other while smiling. Both men have been at loggerheads as Governor Uzodinma has continued to probe Okorocha’s administration and taken over assets said to belong to the state government from him.  Source Former governor of Imo State and member representing Imo West Senatorial District, Owelle Rochas Okorocha has denied having any problem with Governor Hope Uzodinma. The senator said rather, Governor Uzodinma is the one creating problems for himself and also inventing problems where they do not exist. Uzodinma had at the… In "News" •Okorocha at the police station Immediate past Governor of Imo State, Senator Rochas Okorocha, has been arrested on the orders of the Imo State Government. He was not, however, handcuffed as reported by some news platforms. “Yes, it’s true; he has been arrested,” a top State Government official said this… In "Top Stories" Senator Rochas Okorocha has reacted to the arrest of him and his wife and also the demolition of Reach FM's fence, a property reportedly owned by his daughter. Okorocha who was was arrested on Sunday February 21, for unsealing a property seized by the Imo state government and later released… In "Politics"